name: Sydus Art Lora [9mb]
description:
Lora for capturing the SydusArt style which is unique for its artistic and painterly feel, but also for the chromatic aberration style he likes to use to bring different colours into the art.

I'll warn you now, its heavily NSFW because Sydus is a NSFW artist, but you can definitely use prompts to get the clothing you want. Does take a little working with to get right, but definitely gets the look.

Just use the V2 file, its much better than the original.

This LoRA was made on 8dim, hence the small file size (Its not a virus). Refer to this link if you are still unsure about small LoRA. https://civitai.com/models/6596/luisap-lora-dont-need-to-be-bigger-new-recipe


I used OrangeCocoa5050 to train and used 512x512 to train.

For V1 I got the best results using 512x768 res, 0.7 Strength, HiRes fix works wonders as well as including: Sydus, chromatic aberration, and watercolor (Or pretty much just anything to get the painterly look)

For V2 you do not require any prompts and you will be fine with 0.5-0.7 weighting. If you want stronger artstyle, you can still prompt in Chromatic aberration if you want.


If you have any LoRA requests and wouldnt mind buying me a Hot Chocolate, please consider going to my page. https://www.buymeacoffee.com/JohnStinko
